MEASUREMENTS (
MM
).—N = five males or five females, mean (range). Length of body: males 19.05 (18.55– 19.80), female 20.65 (19.50–22.00); length of fore wing: males 24.40 (24.15–25.15), female 25.62 (24.05–26.45); width of fore wing: males 9.10 (8.90–9.40), female 9.51 (8.80–9.85); length of head: males 3.24 (3.15–3.35), female 3.28 (3.05–3.45); width of head including eyes: males 6.42 (6.20–6.55), female 6.54 (6.30–6.75); width of pronotum including suprahumeral plates: males 8.25 (8.00–8.60), female 8.33 (7.70–8.75); width of mesonotum: males 7.19 (6.95–7.40), female 7.33 (6.80–7.70).
